Package com.company.Annotation_2

Interface AnimeCharacter

All Known Implementing Classes:
Gohan, Goku, Trunks, Vegeta
@Preamble(date="16/10/2024", author="Goku", currentRevision=1, lastModified="N\\A", reviewers="Vegeta") public interface AnimeCharacter
The AnimeCharacter interface represents a blueprint for all anime characters, defining key methods like PowerLevel and currentForm that any implementing class must provide.

Classes like Goku and Vegeta implement this interface to define their unique power levels and forms. Other classes can also implement this interface to model different anime characters.

This interface is annotated with the @Preamble annotation to provide additional metadata about its creation.

Interface Methods:

  • PowerLevel(): This method is intended to return the power level of the anime character when implemented.
  • currentForm(): This method is intended to print or return the current transformation form of the anime character.

Static Methods:

  • callAllMethods(Goku myCat): This is a static utility method that currently does not perform any actions, but it can be modified to execute multiple methods on an instance of Goku or other classes implementing AnimeCharacter.

Usage:

Any class that implements AnimeCharacter must provide implementations for the methods PowerLevel() and currentForm().

For example: 

 
 public class Goku implements AnimeCharacter {
     @Override
     public void PowerLevel() {
         System.out.println("Power Level: 5000001");
     }
     @Override
     public void currentForm() {
         System.out.println("Current Form: Ultra Instinct");
     }
 }

Likewise, other characters like Vegeta can provide their own implementations.

Annotated with @Preamble to document authorship and review details.
